<item>
            <title>[SOLR-348] faceting, highlighting, mlt, should short circut when no matches</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-348</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;all code in the core handlers that operates on the DocSet or DocList produced from a &quot;main&quot; serach should be smart enough to give up immediately when the DocList/DocSet is empty.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;optimizations could be put in the handlers, but the definitely need to be put in the utility classes (so consumer written handlers benefit as well)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Slow-response-tf4394686.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Slow-response-tf4394686.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
